0:Nishijou Takumi's alma mater, Kitazawa Second Elementary School, was about a five minute walk from the private train station.\p;
100:Ban Yasuji had attempted to contact Takumi's elementary school teacher over the phone, only to be told that they had unfortunately passed away.\p;
200:Left with no other choice, Ban had decided to set up a meeting to speak with the person who had answered the phone instead—the head teacher, Kamio. Not long after, he had arrived at the school together with his partner.\p;
300:As it was a Saturday, the school gate was closed. The two detectives, Ban and Suwa, stopped in front of it and turned their attention toward the school building.\p;
400:The white walls of the school's exterior had been painted with a brightly colored, eye-catching mural.\p;
500:Due to his complete lack of knowledge on paintings or any other kind of fine art, Ban had no idea what it signified, but the way the spiral-shaped mural transitioned vertically into an array of seven different colors reminded him of a rainbow.\p;
